{"key":"processedPost-9977040","value":{"id":9977040,"first":9976644,"last":9977040,"when":1237154866,"utime":"03/16/09 01:07 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />so i was wondering if i could just put a water source inside the box itself and use a fish tank bubbler to produce the moisture in the air to use as a substitute for the misting. would this work? </blockquote><br />No.&nbsp; For proper pinning performance, your cakes need to dry out slightly, and then have that moisture replaced. This is the number 1 pinning trigger. If you gave them a steady stream of water to prevent drying, performance would be poor, or non-existent.&nbsp; You need to mist.&nbsp; The level of automation to duplicate the human eyeballs and brain/hand coordination hasn't been developed yet.<br />RR","title":"Re: grow box question"}}